&=\frac{1}{2}\int_{0}^{1}dx\int_{0}^{1 - x}(1 - x - y)^2dy\\
&=\frac{1}{2}\int_{0}^{1}\left[-\frac{1}{3}(1 - x - y)^3\right]_{y = 0}^{y = 1 - x}dx\\
&=\frac{1}{6}\int_{0}^{1}(1 - x)^3dx=\frac{1}{24}
\end{align*}
因此$I = 6\times\frac{1}{24}=\frac{1}{4}$.

